  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at this assurance tier. Decision: Accepted. NOTE (adversarial): the ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges in narrative form (temperature 35–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, flow regime 3–8 L/min, rotational speed 2000–3500 RPM) but no hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted, leaving the model's bounded domain of validity formally unspecified per W-ON-02.",
