      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selection of turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive law must be justified by sensitivity analysis and literature evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating pump flows. Sensitivity analysis comparing Giersiepen-Wurzinger and modified power-law hemolysis models shows less than 8% difference in NIH; the more conservative model is adopted."
