    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across verification, validation, and UQ activities. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrates that the 95% credible interval on predicted hemolysis index lies below the absolute clinical threshold across all 5 COU operating points. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility for its intended use in supporting Class III VAD regulatory submission. No unresolved epistemic gaps remain at the assessed model risk level.",
